    "product_description_tabs_tqRhX7": {
      "type": "product-description-tabs",
      "name": "Product Desc Tabs",
      "settings": {
        "description_content": "Shop 14K solid gold hinged segment clicker rings at Monster Piercing. Hypoallergenic, nickel-free, and available in multiple gauges and sizes for helix, septum, and ear piercings. Free UK delivery over £20.",
        "specifications_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"specifications\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"10\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f5f5f5;\">\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Attribute</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Details</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Material</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">14K Solid Gold (100% Nickel-Free)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Finish</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">High-Polish</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Available Colours</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yellow Gold, White Gold, Rose Gold</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Body Location</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nose, Ear, Helix, Septum, Cartilage, Tragus, Daith</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Available Gauges</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">16G (1.2mm), 18G (1.0mm), 20G (0.8mm)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Available Inner Diameters</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm, 7mm, 8mm, 9mm, 10mm, 11mm, 12mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Design Type</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hinged Segment Clicker</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Sold As</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Single Piece</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Biocompatible</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hypoallergenic, 100% Nickel-Free, Skin-Safe</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "features_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"features\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <ul style=\"line-height: 1.8;\">\n<li>\n<strong>14K Solid Gold Construction:</strong> Premium material ensures longevity, biocompatibility, and lasting lustre across years of daily wear.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>100% Nickel-Free:</strong> Hypoallergenic composition suitable for sensitive skin, newly healed piercings, and individuals with metal allergies.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Hinged Opening Mechanism:</strong> Allows effortless insertion and removal without twisting or manipulation, reducing pressure on healing piercings.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Segment Detail:</strong> Curved, decorative front section adds visual interest and style versatility across minimalist and maximalist curation.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Multiple Gauge &amp; Size Options:</strong> Three gauges (16G, 18G, 20G) and five inner diameter sizes (6mm–12mm) accommodate diverse body placements and fit preferences.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Colour Variety:</strong> Yellow, white, and rose gold options support mixed-metal styling and personal aesthetic preferences.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "how_to_use_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"how-to-use\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <ol style=\"line-height: 1.8;\">\n<li>\n<strong>Verify Gauge &amp; Size Compatibility:</strong> Confirm your piercing gauge (16G, 18G, or 20G) and inner diameter (6mm–12mm) using the size guide below. Measure existing jewellery if uncertain.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Inspect the Hinged Mechanism:</strong> Before insertion, ensure the hinged segment is clean and moves smoothly. A responsive hinge ensures comfortable wear.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Insert Through Piercing:</strong> Hold the ring steady and gently slide the opening through your piercing. The hinged design minimises pressure, reducing discomfort.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Position &amp; Seat:</strong> Once through the piercing, rotate the ring to position the segment detail where desired. For helix piercings, the segment typically faces forward or slightly outward.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Verify Secure Fit:</strong> Gently tug to confirm the clicker sits securely without rotation. A properly sized ring should feel snug without pinching or excessive movement.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Inspect After Wear:</strong> Before removing, check that the hinged mechanism remains clean and free of debris. Remove carefully to avoid snagging the piercing.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "care_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"care-instructions\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <ul style=\"line-height: 1.8;\">\n<li>\n<strong>Regular Cleaning:</strong> Remove the clicker and soak in warm water with mild soap for 5–10 minutes weekly. Use a soft-bristled toothbrush to gently scrub the hinged mechanism and segment detail.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Rinse &amp; Dry:</strong> Rinse thoroughly under clean, lukewarm water. Pat dry immediately with a soft, lint-free cloth to prevent water spots and tarnishing.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Avoid Harsh Chemicals:</strong> Do not expose to chlorine, saltwater, perfume, or harsh cleaning products. Remove before swimming, showering, or contact with chemicals.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>No Ultrasonic or Steam Cleaning:</strong> Avoid ultrasonic cleaners and steam cleaning, which can damage the gold surface and compromise the hinged mechanism.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Storage:</strong> Store in a dry, dark location in a soft pouch or jewellery box. Protect from direct sunlight to prevent fading and preserve lustre.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Minimal Polishing:</strong> Allow natural patina to develop; this adds character. If polishing is desired, use only gold-specific polishing cloths and gentle pressure.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Remove During Sleep &amp; Sports:</strong> Avoid sleeping with the clicker in place. Remove during gym sessions, sports, or activities involving hand-to-ear contact to protect the hinged mechanism and piercing.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Saline Soaks for New Piercings:</strong> For newly healed piercings (first 3–6 months), soak twice weekly in sterile saline solution to support healing and prevent irritation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "materials_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"materials-quality\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"10\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f5f5f5;\">\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Material Property</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">14K Gold</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Why It Matters for Piercing Jewellery</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Gold Content</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">58.3% pure gold + alloy metals</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">High gold content ensures biocompatibility and resistance to corrosion; alloy metals provide durability for daily wear.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Nickel Content</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">0% (100% Nickel-Free)</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Eliminates allergic reactions and irritation common in nickel-containing jewellery; essential for sensitive wearers and new piercings.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Hardness</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Moderate (ideal for hinged mechanisms)</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Softer than pure gold but harder than 18K; allows the hinged segment to flex without breaking; resistant to excessive scratching.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Corrosion Resistance</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Excellent (resistant to tarnishing)</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">14K gold resists tarnishing and oxidation; maintains lustre with minimal maintenance across years of wear, including exposure to water and skin acids.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Biocompatibility</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hypoallergenic &amp; Skin-Safe</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gold is well-tolerated by human tissue; suitable for long-term wear, sensitive piercings, and individuals with metal sensitivities or allergies.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Colour Stability</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Develops natural patina with age</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Unlike plated jewellery, 14K gold does not wear away; patina (slight darkening) is normal and valued by collectors as a sign of authenticity and wear.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "ideal_usages_content": "<div class=\"tab-content\" id=\"ideal-usages\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <p><strong>Best Suited For:</strong></p>\n<ul style=\"line-height: 1.8;\">\n<li>\n<strong>Helix &amp; Upper Ear Piercings:</strong> The curved profile of the hinged clicker flatters helix anatomy. The 18G or 20G gauge with 8mm–10mm diameters creates proportionate, elegant positioning along the ear curve.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Septum Piercings:</strong> The compact hinged design suits septum placements without excessive visibility or discomfort. The 18G 8mm–9mm configuration is ideal for standard septum anatomy.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Cartilage &amp; Tragus:</strong> Thicker cartilage anatomy benefits from the 16G gauge and 9mm–11mm diameters, ensuring secure fit without pressure or rotation.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Newly Healed Piercings:</strong> The hinged mechanism allows gentle insertion without twisting, reducing trauma to healing tissue. The hypoallergenic 14K gold composition supports uninterrupted healing.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Long-Term Wear:</strong> Professional piercers recommend 14K gold for permanent collection pieces. The biocompatible material and durable construction ensure years of comfortable, irritation-free wear.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Sensitive Skin &amp; Metal Allergies:</strong> 100% nickel-free composition eliminates common allergens; ideal for wearers with documented metal sensitivities or inflammatory skin conditions.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Mixed-Metal Curation:</strong> The hinged clicker pairs beautifully with silver, rose gold, titanium, and gemstone pieces for contemporary, eclectic ear stacks.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Collection Milestones:</strong> Suitable as a gift to celebrate first piercings, healed piercings, stretched lobes, or personal identity expression through body jewellery.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "size_guide_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"gauge-size-guide\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"10\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f5f5f5;\">\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gauge</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Millimetres (mm)</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Inches</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Best For</th>\n<th style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Available Inner Diameters</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>16G</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">1.2mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">0.048\"</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thicker cartilage, tragus, standard ear lobes (non-stretched)</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm, 7mm, 8mm, 9mm, 10mm, 11mm, 12mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>18G</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">1.0mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">0.040\"</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Standard helix, septum, nostril, and most ear piercings</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm, 7mm, 8mm, 9mm, 10mm, 11mm, 12mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>20G</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">0.8mm</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">0.032\"</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Delicate ear piercings, nostril, stretched lobes (small gauge)</td>\n<td style=\"border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">6mm, 7mm, 8mm, 9mm, 10mm, 11mm, 12mm</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 15px;\"><strong>How to Measure Inner Diameter:</strong> Measure the distance across the ring opening (from one side of the inner curve to the opposite side). Place a ruler or calliper against the inside of an existing ring that fits comfortably. If unsure, consult with your piercing professional—they can measure your piercing and recommend the exact gauge and diameter.</p>\n<p><strong>Important:</strong> Gauge and inner diameter are independent measurements. Always verify both before purchasing. A ring that is the correct gauge but wrong diameter will not fit properly.</p>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>",
        "faq_content": "<div class=\"tab-content active\" id=\"faq\">\n                  <!-- BEGIN app snippet: tab-content -->\n\n\n  <ul class=\"faq-list\">\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Is 14K gold hypoallergenic and suitable for sensitive skin?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Yes. This clicker is 100% nickel-free and crafted from premium 14K solid gold, making it hypoallergenic and suitable for sensitive skin, metal allergies, and newly healed piercings. Nickel is a common allergen in body jewellery; eliminating it entirely ensures compatibility for wearers with sensitivities. However, if you have a documented metal allergy, consult your piercer or dermatologist before wearing.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What is the difference between a hinged clicker and a seamless ring?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>A hinged clicker features a mechanism that opens slightly, allowing the ring to slide through your piercing without twisting or bending. Seamless rings are continuous circles with no opening and require rotation during insertion, which can cause discomfort or trauma to healing tissue. The hinged design makes insertion gentler and faster—ideal for new piercings and everyday wearability.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Which gauge and size should I choose?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Your piercing gauge (measured in millimetres) and inner diameter (the opening size) are critical. Measure your existing jewellery or consult your piercer for exact measurements. The Gauge Size Guide tab above shows recommended gauges by body location. If you're unsure, contact Monster Piercing customer service with your piercing location and existing jewellery details for a sizing recommendation.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            How long will 14K gold last with daily wear?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>14K gold is durable for daily wear and, with proper care, will last for decades. Unlike plated jewellery, solid gold does not wear away; it develops a natural patina with age, adding character. The hinged mechanism is designed to withstand repeated opening and closing when cared for properly (avoid sleeping with the ring in place and remove during sports or high-impact activities).</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Can I shower or swim with the 14K gold clicker?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Freshwater exposure is generally safe for 14K gold. However, remove the clicker before swimming in chlorinated pools or saltwater, as these environments can accelerate tarnishing and affect the hinged mechanism. Avoid exposing to perfume, lotions, and harsh chemicals. For showering, occasional brief exposure is fine, but remove regularly to extend longevity.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            How do I clean and maintain the hinged mechanism?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Soak the clicker in warm water with mild soap for 5–10 minutes, then use a soft-bristled toothbrush to gently scrub the hinge and segment detail. Rinse thoroughly and pat dry immediately. Do not use ultrasonic cleaners, steam cleaners, or abrasive polishing compounds. Store in a dry location away from sunlight. The hinge should move smoothly; if it becomes stiff, soak again and gently work the mechanism until it opens freely.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Is this clicker suitable for newly pierced ears?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Yes. The hinged mechanism allows gentle insertion without twisting, reducing trauma to healing tissue. The 100% nickel-free, hypoallergenic 14K gold composition supports uninterrupted healing. For newly pierced ears (typically healing 6–12 weeks), soak the clicker twice weekly in sterile saline solution to support healing and prevent irritation. Consult your piercer for specific aftercare guidance.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What is the difference between yellow, white, and rose gold?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>All three options are 14K solid gold with identical material properties and biocompatibility. Yellow gold has warm tone, white gold has cool tone, and rose gold has romantic warm-pink tone. The choice is purely aesthetic and depends on your skin undertone, personal style, and how you want the piece to coordinate with other jewellery. All three are hypoallergenic and durable.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            Can I wear the clicker in multiple piercings?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Yes. The hinged segment clicker's versatile design suits helix, septum, cartilage, tragus, daith, and nostril placements. You can rotate it between piercings by removing and reinserting, or purchase multiple sizes and gauges to wear across piercings simultaneously. Each removal requires measuring and verifying gauge and diameter compatibility with the intended piercing.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n      <li class=\"faq-item\">\n        <details>\n          <summary>\n            What is your return policy if the fit isn't right?\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"faq-icon\" viewbox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#666\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"animation: auto ease 0s 1 normal none running none;\"><polyline points=\"6 9 12 15 18 9\"></polyline></svg>\n          </summary>\n          <div class=\"faq-answer\">\n            <p>Not specified in provided data. Please contact Monster Piercing customer service for details on return eligibility, timeframes, and conditions. Most reputable body jewellery retailers offer returns for unused items within 14–30 days. If the clicker arrives damaged or with manufacturing defects, contact customer service immediately for replacement or refund.</p>\n          </div>\n        </details>\n      </li>\n    \n  </ul>\n\n<!-- END app snippet -->\n                </div>"
      }
    }
  },
